e computed the dynamics of nucleosomes for this model, using continuous time stochastic simulations (31,32). n brief, at each step of the computation, we use the rates of the events which are possible, to compute the time interval until the next stochastically determined on-, off- or slide event. he event is then implemented, and the time is updated. uccessive events are considered to be uncorrelated.  hydrolysis, while not explicitly included in the kinetic model, is implicitly included through the non-thermal remodeling (eviction and sliding) processes (17).
